# Orchestrator Skill Definition

## Overview
This template defines the structure of an orchestrator skill that coordinates other skills.

## Core Responsibilities
- Coordinate skill execution order
- Manage state between skills
- Handle error recovery and fallbacks
- Track execution metrics

## Input Schema
```yaml
{
  "task": "string - what to orchestrate",
  "params": "object - parameters for sub-skills",
  "config": "object - orchestration configuration"
}
```

## Output Schema
```yaml
{
  "status": "success|error|partial",
  "results": "object - aggregated results from all skills",
  "execution_trace": "array - trace of skill execution",
  "metrics": "object - timing and performance data"
}
```

## Sub-Skills to Coordinate
- {SKILL_1}
- {SKILL_2}
- {SKILL_3}

## Execution Flow
```
[Start] → [Skill A] → [Skill B] → [Skill C] → [Aggregation] → [End]
```

## Error Handling
```
{ERROR_HANDLING_STRATEGY}
